   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the lower front plate in the I/O section.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_75-100_nam_install_power_cables_remove_plate_120mm_0000105550.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the equipment grounding conductor to the ground
busbar.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet Without Transformer</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_pxc_nam_75-100_kva_connect_ground_input_bypass_cables_w120mm__0000105529.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet Without Transformer</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_pxc_nam_75-100_kva_connect_output_and_battery_cables_w120mm_0000105528.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Busbars in UPS With Transformer –
Single Mains</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_nam_75-100_single_mains_ups_busbars_for_measurements_120mm_0000181044.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Busbars in UPS With Transformer –
Dual Mains</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_nam_75-100_dual_mains_ups_busbars_for_measurements_120mm_0000181043.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of Busbars on Transformers</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_nam_75-100_transformer_busbars_for_measurements_120mm_0000181042.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Use a probe to measure for voltages and currents at the
busbars:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>UPS input at input L1, input L2, input L3 , and input
N.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Bypass at bypass L1, bypass L2, bypass L3, and bypass
N.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>UPS output at output L1, output L2, output L3, and output
N.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Battery DC at battery + and battery - .</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Transformer input at input H1, input H2, input H3, and
input N H0.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Transformer bypass at bypass H1, bypass H2, bypass H3,
and bypass N H0.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Transformer output at output X1,output X2, output X3,
and output N X0.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
            <stepxmp>
               <hazardstatement type="danger">
                  <messagepanel>
                     <typeofhazard>HAZARD OF ELECTRIC SHOCK, EXPLOSION, OR ARC FLASH</typeofhazard>
                     <howtoavoid>Measure voltages and currents on all busbars. The battery
busbars for adjacent battery cabinets are placed in the power section
of the UPS cabinet.</howtoavoid>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet - Adjacent Battery Busbars</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_pxc_nam_75-100_kva_adjacent_battery_cabinet_connect_power_cables_120mm_0000134961.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
